						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">Gilded pandas are highly opportunistic, capable of eating anything.</cell>
						<br />
						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">The first reports of gilded pandas date back to the famed explorer Fooleesh J. Ester in the European Alps.</cell>
						<br />
						<cell pady="10" width="32">
							<img sh="32" src="ui/zoopedia/fact-bullet.tga" sw="32" sx="0" sy="0" />
						</cell>
						<cell pady="10" width="202">In spite of the natural durability of gold, gilded pandas are no less fragile than their Chinese counterparts..
</cell>
						<br />
					</cell>
